wiki.summary: "Praise God" is the sixth track from Kanye West's 2021 album Donda. The track features Travis Scott, who began his career as a signee to Ye's label G.O.O.D. Music, and Baby Keem. It also begins with a snippet from a lecture given by Donda West, part of which is sampled for the hook. "Praise God" was first heard during the July 22nd listening party at Mercedes-Benz Stadium in Atlanta, GA. Travis Scott featured much more prominently on this version of the track Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Praise God" is the sixth track from Kanye West's 2021 album Donda. The track features Travis Scott, who began his career as a signee to Ye's label G.O.O.D. Music, and Baby Keem. It also begins with a snippet from a lecture given by Donda West, part of which is sampled for the hook. "Praise God" was first heard during the July 22nd listening party at Mercedes-Benz Stadium in Atlanta, GA. Travis Scott featured much more prominently on this version of the track, with subsequent versions (including the official release) having more of an interplay between him and Kanye.
